"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-soccer-news-which-teams-have-qualified-for-the-2024-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"The 2024 Olympics in Paris are in full flow and the soccer tournaments have been absolutely enthralling.  And now we are into the final few games, with the bronze and gold medal matches taking place over the next few days.  [ LIVE:Watch every soccer game at Paris 2024 Olympics]  With stadiums across France (Bordeaux, Lyon, Nice, Marseille, Nantes and Saint-Etienne will host games) being used and the final held at Paris Saint-Germain's Parc des Princes home, this has been an epic celebration of the beautiful game.  [ MORE:How does it work?]  Below you will find details on who has qualified for the 2024 Olympics in both the men's and women's soccer tournaments, while you can click on the link for details about how to watch all of the Olympic action across NBC's platforms.    Dates: July 25 - August 10TV: USA Network, E!, other NBC channelsOnline:Watch on Peacock    Bronze medal match  Friday, August 9: Spain 0-1 Germany (Lyon) -Recap & highlights  Gold medal match  Saturday, August 10: Brazil 0-1 USA (Paris) -Recap, highlights & analysis    Bronze medal match  Thursday, August 8: Egypt 0-6 Morocco (Nantes)- Morocco wins bronze medal  Gold medal match  Friday, August 9: France 3-5 (AET) Spain (Paris) -Highlights, recap & analysis-Spain wins gold medal, France wins silver    Semifinals  Tuesday, August 6: USA 1-0 (AET) Germany (Lyon) -Recap, highlights, analysisTuesday, August 6: Spain 2-4 Brazil (Marseille)  Quarterfinals  Quarterfinal 2: Saturday, August 3: USA 1-0 (AET) Japan (Paris) -Highlights, recap & analysisQuarterfinal 3: Saturday, August 3: Spain 2-2 (4-2 PKs) Colombia (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 4: Saturday, August 3: Canada 0-0 (2-4 PKs) Germany (Marseille) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 1: Saturday, August 3: France 0-1 Brazil (Nantes) -Recap & highlights  Thursday, July 25  Canada 2-1 New Zealand (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlightsFrance 3-2 Colombia (Lyon) -Recap & highlights  Sunday, July 28  New Zealand 0-2 Colombia (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsFrance 1-2 Canada (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlights  Wednesday, July 31  New Zealand 1-2 France (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsColombia 0-1 Canada (Nice) -Recap & highlights  Thursday, July 25  Germany 3-0 Australia (Marseille) -Recap & highlightsUSA 3-0 Zambia (Nice) -Recap, highlights & analysis  Sunday, July 28  Australia 6-5 Zambia (Nice) -Recap & highlightsUSA 4-1 Germany (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysis  Wednesday, July 31  Zambia 1-4 Germany (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlightsAustralia vs USA, 1pm (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysis  Thursday, July 25  Spain 2-1 Japan (Nantes) -Recap & highlightsNigeria 0-1 Brazil (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights  Sunday, July 28  Brazil 1-2 Japan (Paris) -Recap & highlightsSpain 1-0 Nigeria (Nantes) -Recap & highlights  Wednesday, July 31  Japan 3-1 Nigeria (Nantes) -Recap & highlightsBrazil 0-2 Spain (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights    Quarterfinals  Quarterfinal 2: Friday, August 2: Morocco 4-0 USA, 9am ET (Paris) -Highlights, recap & analysisQuarterfinal 4: Friday, August 2: Japan 0-3 Spain (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 3: Friday, August 2: Egypt 1-1 (5-4 PKs) Paraguay (Marseille) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 1: Friday, August 2: France 1-0 Argentina (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights  Semifinals  Monday, August 5: Morocco 1-2 Spain (Marseille)Monday, August 5: France 3-1 Egypt (Lyon) AET  Wednesday, July 24  Guinea 1-2 New Zealand (Nice) -Recap & highlightsFrance 3-0 USA (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysis  Saturday, July 27  New Zealand 1-4 USA (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysisFrance 1-0 Guinea (Nice) -Recap & highlights  Tuesday, July 30  New Zealand 0-3 France (Marseille)USA 3-0 Guinea (Saint-Etienne) -Recap, highlights & analysis  Wednesday, July 24  Argentina 1-2 Morocco (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlightsIraq 2-1 Ukraine (Lyon) -Recap & highlights  Saturday, July 27  Argentina 3-1 Iraq (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsUkraine 2-1 Morocco (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlights  Tuesday, July 30  Ukraine 0-2 Argentina (Lyon)Morocco 3-0 Iraq (Nice)  Wednesday, July 24  Uzbekistan 1-2 Spain (Paris) -Recap & highlightsEgypt 0-0 Dominican Republic (Nantes) -Recap & highlights  Saturday, July 27  Dominican Republic 1-3 Spain (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlightsUzbekistan 0-1 Egypt (Nantes) -Recap & highlights  Tuesday, July 30  Dominican Republic 1-1 Uzbekistan - (Paris)Spain 1-2 Egypt - (Bordeaux)  Wednesday, July 24  Japan 5-0 Paraguay (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlightsMali 1-1 Israel (Paris) -Recap & highlights  Saturday, July 27  Israel 2-4 Paraguay (Paris) -Recap & highlightsJapan 1-0 Mali (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights  Tuesday, July 30  Paraguay 1-0 Mali (Paris)Israel 0-1 Japan (Nantes)    For the first time since 2008 the USMNT have qualified for the tournament and there will be hopes that a talented young squad can deliver a medal for Team USA as they were handed a kind group stage draw where they face hosts France in the opening game. Two-time reigning champs Brazil failed to qualify so hosts France and reigning World Cup champs Argentina are the favorites to win gold. The men's tournament is a U-23 competition but three players in each squad over the age of 23 are allowed to compete for their nations. With Achraf Hakimi, Michael Olise, Julian Alvarez and plenty of other stars competing in the men's tournament, it's going to be a beauty.  [ MORE:United States men's roster for 2024 Paris Olympics]  The USWNT have qualified for the women's tournament (which allows players of all ages to compete) and are favorites to win gold in Paris under new head coach Emma Hayes, but they have not tasted success at the Olympics since 2012 in London as Canada are the reigning champs. The USWNT were handed a very tough group with Germany, Australia and Zambia set to push them all the way to reach the knockout rounds. Hosts France are also expected to make a deep run, while Canada, Brazil, reigning World Cup champs Spain and Japan are all expected to push for the gold medal.  There are 12 teams in the women's tournament with the USWNT clinching their qualifying spot by winning the CONCACAF W Championship in 2022. Canada beat Jamaica in a CONCACAF playoff as the reigning champs reached the Olympics, while Brazil and Colombia will represent South America. France qualify as hosts, while Germany and Spain qualified as UEFA Nations League Finals third-place winner and finalist respectively. New Zealand represent the Oceania region, while Japan and Australia will represent Asia and Nigeria and Zambia will fly the flag for Africa after coming out of their qualifying tournament.  AFC (Asia): Japan, Australia  CAF (Africa): Nigeria, Zambia  CONMEBOL (South America): Brazil, Colombia  CONCACAF (Central & North America): Canada, USA  OFC (Oceania): New Zealand  UEFA: France (host), Spain, Germany    Group stage draw    Group A: France, Colombia, Canada, New Zealand  Group B: USWNT, Zambia, Germany, Australia  Group C: Spain, Japan, Nigeria,Brazil  There are 16 teams in the men's tournament with three teams from Asia, Africa and Europe, plus two from South America and Central and North America, one from Oceania and France as hosts, qualifying for the tournament. The final team to make it was Guinea as they won the AFC-CAF playoff.    AFC (Asia): Iraq, Japan, Uzbekistan  CAF (Africa): Egypt, Mali, Morocco  CONMEBOL (South America): Argentina, Paraguay  CONCACAF (Central & North America): Dominican Republic, USA  OFC (Oceania): New Zealand  UEFA (Europa): France (host), Israel, Spain, Ukraine  AFC-CAF playoff: Guinea    Group stage draw    Group A: France, USA, Guinea, New Zealand  Group B: Argentina, Morocco, Iraq, Ukraine  Group C: Uzbekistan, Spain, Egypt, Dominican Republic  Group D: Japan, Paraguay, Mali, Israel  A Division ofNBCUniversal.  DISCLAIMER: This site and the products offered are for entertainment purposes only, and there is no gambling offered on this site. This service is intended for adult audiences. No guarantees are made for any specific outcome. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, please call 1-800-GAMBLER.  \\u24b8 2024 NBC Universal\"}"